{{About|the Dutch archaeologist|the German author|Corinne Hofmann}} [[File:CorinneHofman2014.jpg|thumb|Corinne Hofman (2014)]] '''Corinne Lisette Hofman''' (born 10 July 1959) is a Dutch professor of Caribbean Archaeology at [[Leiden University]] since 2007. She was a winner of the 2014 [[Spinoza Prize]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.nwo.nl/en/research-and-results/programmes/spinoza+prize/spinoza+laureates/overview+in+alphabetical+order/corinne+hofman |title=Prof. C.L. (Corinne) Hofman |publisher=[[Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research]] |date=28 August 2014 |accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>
Hofman was born in [[Wassenaar]]. She obtained a PhD at Leiden University in 1993.<ref>[http://hoogleraren.leidenuniv.nl/id/3574 Corinne Lisette Hofman] at ''Leiden Faculty from 1575'' website</ref>
In 2013 Hofman won the Merian Prize of the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]]. The Merian Prize is awarded to excelling women scientists, inspiring others for a career in science.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.knaw.nl/nl/actueel/nieuws/knaw-merianprijs-voor-caribisch-archeologe-corinne-hofman |title=KNAW Merianprijs voor Caribisch archeologe Corinne Hofman |language=Dutch |publisher=[[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] |date=19 September 2013 |accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>
In 2014 she was one of four winners of the Dutch [[Spinoza Prize]] and received a 2,5 million euro grant.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.nwo.nl/en/research-and-results/programmes/spinoza+prize/spinoza+laureates/overview+by+year/2014 |title=NWO Spinoza Prize 2014 |publisher=Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research |date=11 September 2014 |accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>
Since 2015 Hofman is member of the Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.knaw.nl/nl/leden/leden/14385 |title=Corinne Hofman |language=Dutch |publisher=Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences |date= |accessdate=25 June 2015}}</ref>
