[[File:Bogan House, Totnes (geograph 4503727).jpg|thumb|Bogan House]] {{Costume}} The '''Devonshire Collection of Period Costume'''<ref name="culture24">[http://www.culture24.org.uk/sw000038 Devonshire Collection of Period Costume], [[Culture 24]], UK.</ref> is a collection of historic [[costume]]s housed in the '''Totnes Fashion and Textiles Museum''' in the town of [[Totnes]], south [[Devon]], in southwest [[England]].<ref>[http://www.visitsouthdevon.co.uk/ South Devon Culture], UK.</ref>
The collection includes [[clothing]] for men, women, and children, dating from the 18th century to the end of the 20th century.<ref name="culture24" /> An annually updated exhibition is displayed in Bogan House, a Tudor merchant's house at 43 High Street, Totnes.<ref>[http://www.devon.gov.uk/museums_south_hams/mus_totnes_costume.htm Totnes Costume Museum] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615161403/http://www.devon.gov.uk/museums_south_hams/mus_totnes_costume.htm |date=2011-06-15 }}, [http://www.devon.gov.uk/ Devon County Council], UK.</ref>
