'''John Emery Murdoch''' (May 10, 1927 – September 16, 2010) was an American academic.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.extension.harvard.edu/hub/news/remembering-longtime-faculty-member-john-e-murdoch |title=Remembering Longtime Faculty Member John E. Murdoch |publisher=Extension.harvard.edu |date=2010-09-21 |accessdate=2014-03-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140305082822/http://www.extension.harvard.edu/hub/news/remembering-longtime-faculty-member-john-e-murdoch |archivedate=2014-03-05 |df= }}</ref><ref name=EarlyScienceObit>{{cite journal|last=Thijssen|first=Hans|author2=Lüthy, Christoph|title=John Emery Murdoch (10 May 1927–16 September 2010)|journal=Early Science and Medicine|date=1 March 2011|volume=16|issue=2|pages=147–152|doi=10.1163/157338211X557093}}</ref><ref name=Speculum>{{cite journal|last=McVaugh|first=M R|author2=Sylla, E D |author3=Grant, E |title=Memoirs of Fellows and Corresponding Fellows of the Medieval Academy of America John Emery Murdoch|journal=Speculum: A Journal of Medieval Studies|date=Jul 2011|volume=86|issue=3|pages=855–857}}</ref> Educated in philosophy at the [[University of Wisconsin&ndash;Madison]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fas.harvard.edu/~hsdept/bios/murdoch.html |title=People - The Department of the History of Science, Harvard University |publisher=Fas.harvard.edu |date=2010-09-16 |accessdate=2014-03-05}}</ref> Murdoch spent most of his career at [[Harvard University]].<ref name=Speculum /> At Harvard, he was Professor of History of Science and Chair of the Department from 1966 to 1971 and 1974 to 1975.<ref>{{cite web|last=Sweeney |first=Sarah |url=http://news.harvard.edu/gazette/story/2010/09/john-e-murdoch-obituary/ |title=John E. Murdoch, professor of history of science, 83 &#124; Harvard Gazette |publisher=News.harvard.edu |accessdate=2014-03-05}}</ref> He specialized in ancient and medieval medicine and philosophy,<ref>{{cite web|last=McAuley |first=James K. |url=http://www.thecrimson.com/article