[[File:Ruins of pavilion near Mahram nagar or IGI Airport.jpg|thumb|400px|right|Ruins of pavilion at [[Mehram Serai]] near [[Indira Gandhi International Airport|IGI Terminal-1]].]]
'''Mehram Nagar''', a 17th century village, lies north-east of [[Indira Gandhi International Airport|IGI Terminal-1]] in [[Delhi]] state of India.
==History== Mehram Nagar village, Meharm Bazaar and [[Mehram Serai]] were established in 1639 by an eunuch Mehram Khan and till now its not developed ,<ref name=mehr1>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/delhi-news/17th-century-caravanserai-falls-into-ruin-as-delhi-govt-defence-ministry-squabble/story-3qFH6tUbwzQdoCuSHs8vfP.html "17th century inn lies in ruin as Delhi govt, defence ministry squabble."], [[Hindustan Times]], 23 Nov 2017.</ref> who was incharge of mughal harem during the reign of [[Shah Jahan]].<ref name=mehr3>Francis Gladwin, 1788, [https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=GINfAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA62&dq=mehram+serai&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj-2Kf7ktTXAhWBMI8KHTeEC0IQ6AEIJzAA#v=onepage&q=mehram%20serai&f=false "The History of Hindostan, during the reigns of Jehángir, Sháhjehán, and Aurungzebe."].</ref>
[[Archaeological Survey of India]] board in the village mentions several monuments, including the old darwaza (gate), mosque and serai that were built by the mughals, such as Mehram Khan (harem keeper of Jahangir), [[Shah Jahan]] and his son [[Aurangzeb]] in 1660 CE.
